title: Oman Cricket E division: Satham Hussain sets up Fairuz’s victory
text:
Oman Cricket E division: Satham Hussain sets up Fairuz’s victory Nadeem Abdul (left) and Mohammed Amir of Techno Elevators October 13, 2015 
Satham Hussain scored a match-shaping 70 that helped Al Fairuz secure a 58-run win against Majees A in an Oman Cricket E division match at Al Amerat recently. 
After Al Fairuz batted first to make 175 for eight in 20 overs, Majees A was shot out for 117 in 17.2 overs. 
Brief scores: Al Fairuz 175-8 in 20 overs (Hussain 70; Zuhair Moula 2-29) beat Majees A 117 in 17.2 overs (Mohsin Zaidi 31; Manikhandan 3-15). 
Satish Karate of Bank Dhofar 
G division: Trust Oilfield 199-5 in 19 overs (Mushir Nasir 44 n.o; Sreelal 2-31) beat Prime Trading 162 in 18.5 overs (Sanath Nair 29; Shamsudheen Irfan 2-34). 
F division: Kairali 179 in 19.5 overs (Waleed Abdul 45; Biju Velayudhan 3-30, Murtaza Ahmed 3-34) beat Al Daam 160-9 in 20 overs (Shibin Koshi 32; Fahad Hamsa 2-20, Praveen Kumar 2-21). 
H division: Star Care Hospital 167-7 in 20 overs (Shahid Chouhan 34; Umar Rehman 2-29) beat Colour & Design 153-8 in 20 overs (Samir Mohammed 40; Arif Ali 2-20). 
I division: Bank Dhofar 153-7 in 20 overs (Satish Karate 36; Viplav Palai 3-42) beat OHI Douglas 150 in 20 overs (Palai 41; Karate 4-10). 
J division: Techno Elevators 207-5 in 20 overs (Nadeem Abdul 84 n.o; Sayyed Waseem 50) beat Al Nahda 98 in 16 overs (Abdullah Mohammed 32; Mohammed Amir 5-12. 
Girls' U19: Pakistan School Muscat 193-3 in 20 overs (Hira Javed 43) lost to Indian School Muscat 194-2 in 18 overs (Sujana Sundar 69 n.o; Amal Saleem 2-20).
